                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="false">
                                <p>Modern binding, probably 18th century. Light brown leather over wooden boards. 3 double spinebands, 2 endbands. 2 hook-clasp fastenings. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>: traces of a paper label with illegible text. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>: National Library book label with the following text in brown ink: <quote>Teol. Kyrkobr.</quote>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height unit="mm" max="170" min="170"/>
                                        <width unit="mm" max="110" min="110"/>
                                        <depth unit="mm" max="30" min="30"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>Blind tooling. Rectangular panels with ornaments. Four acorns in the corners of the inner frame. In the middle, an oval frame with a cross and the letters <quote>IHS</quote>, surrounded by four trilobed leaves.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Holes caused by insects, especially on <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>.</condition>
                            </binding>
